overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The assistant began by
  analyzing the existing design, identifying areas like the color palette,
  layout, form elements, and overall visual interest as needing improvement. A
  new sleep-themed color palette was introduced, and the main questionnaire form
  was redesigned with decorative elements and an enhanced progress indicator.
  The welcome screen was transformed with feature cards and softer alerts. All
  UI components, including checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards, were
  polished for a more modern and cohesive look. Crucially, all 14 questionnaire
  sections were updated to use consistent, visually appealing card-style
  groupings, replacing the previous plain gray boxes. The report section also
  received a styling update for a more professional appearance. Finally, a
  console error related to null values being passed to input fields was debugged
  and fixed in the  component, ensuring robust form behavior. The overall
  outcome is a visually appealing, calming, and professional sleep health
  questionnaire application.
